tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mild hypoglycemia, elevated creatinine indicating impaired renal function, and metabolic acidosis (low CO₂). Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy with renal impairment. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for underlying diabetes or other causes of renal dysfunction.
